A fork of Zolt√°n Csizmadia's xilprg, supporting NeroJTAG (see http://www.makestuff.eu/wordpress/?page_id=1046).
Because xilprg is not getting updates for new FPGA families, I recommend using FPGALink
(http://www.makestuff.eu/wordpress/?page_id=1400) instead of xilprg, because FPGALink uses .xsvf
files instead of attempting direct support for .bit files, and will thus work for all future FPGA
families.
